social_posts.post_text: 11/27 • On our way to a little Friendsgiving in the park 🤭 It’s not a holiday celebrated here, but it was organized by a sweet new mama friend (hi @julzadastra) who lived in the US before and wanted to bring this tradition to France 🫶🏼 A little late to post, but I’m just so grateful for these boys and the life we are building 🙏🏼 #leslitaise #lennonlitaise

A sweet Sunday “en famille” to celebrate my @antoinelitaise ❤️ What a gift it is to do life with you, to have you by my side…to have fallen in love with you on a whim in a foreign country to now having made a home with you here. You’re the best partner, papa, and best friend that I couldn’t have even dreamt of myself. You make life more fun, easy, and just overall better. Happy (belated) Birthday to my favorite Frenchie 😘 I love you beaucoup! • #leslitaise

Bye bye mullet 👋🏼 Lennon had his first little trim today thanks to @bol_marseille who knew the best way to cut his angel baby hair and was so patient with him 🤎 And yes, I am 100000% “that mom” who kept a lock of his white blonde locks 🥹 On another note, Lennon turned 18 months almost 3 weeks ago and I can’t believe how fast it’s all flying. I know I say that each time, but I truly mean it!! My baby is growing so quickly before my eyes, talking more, wanting to do things more independently, blowing us away with his intelligence and leaving us in stitches with his humor. He is just the right amount of salty and sweet…he is obsessed with mimicking animal sounds (quack quack is his fave 🦆) still has a strong passion for “couteaux” (knives) and motorcycles 🏍️😅…says mama / maman approximately 3,000 times a day and could eat a trio of bell peppers and clementines for every meal if I let him. He loves Daniel Tiger and our morning nursing sessions and being by or in the water…and is honestly just one happy go lucky little boy. It’s wild how he’s only been here a year and a half and yet I can hardly imagine a time he wasn’t with us. You’re just golden, Lenny Loo ✨ • #lennonlitaise #leslitaise #18months #firsthaircut

This boyyyyyyyy 🖤 In two weeks he’ll be two and I just can’t wrap my head around the time that has passed. I’ve said it a million times but I’ll say it again, because it’s worth repeating: Lennon, you are magic 💫

Motherhood has welcomed me into a new dimension of myself that I’ve been so grateful to “meet” 🕊️ I’ve never felt more feminine and into my calling than in my role as a mother…I truly believe that becoming a mom has given me a new lens… one that has allowed me to relive past and present experiences with fresh eyes: the preciousness of life, the intention behind my own’s parent’s choices…the kindness towards ourselves, to the children all around us, and the deep, unconditional love that I’ve come to know and feel and give. 

It’s been a beautiful and at times remarkable journey to watch my body change to adapt to the needs of my child…something I didn’t anticipate before becoming a mother was how much it would continue to evolve in the past almost two years since my boy had been earth-side and as our breastfeeding journey comes to an end. One thing that has always made me feel feminine and confident are well-fitting and beautiful lingerie. Thank you @simoneperele_france for clothing this body that has carried me through the most beautiful season of my life…growing life and mothering 🤱

This boy has brought colors to my world that I didn’t know existed. Motherhood has completely changed me, but it’s Lennon who has especially left an impression. My sweet friend @andannabelle said it best, so I’ll share her words: “It’s crazy how we don’t choose who it is that we are loving, but it’s our greatest love of all…”. Thank you for finding your way to me, Lennon. You make me better 🤍 #happymothersday #letterstolennon

Lenny Loo turned two 💛 (5/27/23) and we celebrated with some close friends + family yesterday at A’s grandparents house. I can’t believe this sweet, rambunctious boy is two already. He’s so full of life, curiosity, and a smile that I swear could melt any soul. His shaggy blonde hair and his animated franglais (French + English) conversations, his obsessions for motorcycles and the way he gasps and says “uh oh” or “look!” or “I did it!” are some of my favorite things about him right now. I never want to forget this version of you, Lennon. Each one is magical in its own way. Happy you, baby boy. Thank you for making me a mama / maman two years ago 🫶🏼 • #letterstolennon #leslitaise

30/8/23 • A little love letter to my sweet boy. I wish I could bottle up your sweet, high-pitched voice…your white blonde wispy locks and that sly smile you give when you’re doing something sneaky. I try to memorize the scent of the top of your head and the sound of your belly laugh or your feet hitting the wooden floors in the morning, to come find me…I love the way you giggle with your hand up to your mouth, the way you mélange French and English in one sentence, calling “hey guys!!!” to your French friends or how you flip your pillow over to the cold side when you’re getting settled for bed. I know it won’t always be this way, these versions of you, but I love each and every one. Watching you become, changing, growing, discovering. You’re curious and clever and creative and kind. You’re full of spirit and energy and I wouldn’t change a single thing about you, my Lennon.
